Class Team

java.lang.Object
Team
public class Team
extends java.lang.Object
This is a container class that defines a team and its operations.
Author:
Haolun Cheng

    • Team

      public Team()

  • Method Details

    • find

      private int find​(TeamMember m)
      Finds the index of team member that needs to be removed from team.
      Parameters:
      team - member object thats needs to be checked in list.
      Returns:
      index if team member found, not found otherwise.

    • grow

      private void grow()
      Increases team length by 4 new indecies. Checks if team length equals number of members, then creates new list and copies old list into new list and re-references.

    • isEmpty

      public boolean isEmpty()
      Checks if the team list is empty.
      Returns:
      true if the team list is empty, false otherwise.

    • add

      public void add​(TeamMember m)
      Appends new team member object to end of array. This methods first checks if there is space in the current list and then appends new item. It also, increases the number of members after appending.
      Parameters:
      new - team member object that needs to be added.

    • remove

      public boolean remove​(TeamMember m)
      Calls find method and finds the index of the team member to be removed. This method inserts the last item in the array to fill the index after object was removed. It then sets the reference of the last item to null and decreases number of members by one.
      Parameters:
      team - member object that needs to be removed.
      Returns:
      true if member was deleted, false otherwise.

    • contains

      public boolean contains​(TeamMember m)
      Checks if the team member list already contains team member object.
      Parameters:
      team - member object that needs to be compared to items in array.
      Returns:
      true if array contains member, false otherwise.

    • print

      public void print()
      Prints the contents of the array toString method to print the objects in the array until array is null or loop reaches end of array.
